2:
For the wicked and deceitful attack me;
\q they speak lies against me.
\q

6:
Appoint a wicked man over such an enemy as these people;
\q appoint an accuser to stand at his right hand.
\q

8:
May his days be few;
\q may another take his office.
\q

11:
May the creditor take all he owns;
\q may strangers plunder what he earns.
\q

12:
May no one extend any kindness to him;
\q may no one have pity on his fatherless children.
\q

14:
May his ancestors' sins be mentioned to Yahweh;
\q and may the sin of his mother not be forgotten.
\q

15:
May their guilt always be before Yahweh;
\q may Yahweh cut off their memory from the earth.
\q

24:
My knees are weak from fasting;
\q I am turning to skin and bones.
\q

26:
Help me, Yahweh my God;
\q save me by your covenant faithfulness.
\q

30:
With my mouth I give great thanks to Yahweh;
\q I will praise him in the midst of a crowd.
\q
